{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, some studies use LoRA to fine-tune Vision Transformer (ViT) for visual tracking [180] and face forgery detection [181].",
    "Multimodal tasksMultimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) aim to integrate text with various modalities such as audio, image and video, which enable cross-modal understanding and reasoning through a unified embedding space.",
    "The success of LoRA in both NLP and vision tasks has sparked considerable interest in applying them to MLLMs.In MLLMs, LoRA can not only improve training efficiency but also facilitate effective modality alignment.",
    "In audio-text tasks, SALM [182] comprises LoRA layers, a frozen textbased LLM, an audio encoder and a modality adapter to handle speech inputs and corresponding task instructions.",
    "For image-text tasks, InternLM-XComposer2 [183] achieves modality alignment by applying LoRA to image tokens, mPLUG-Owl [184] freezes the visual module while jointly fine-tuning LoRA and abstractor of the text module, and CoLLaVO [185] employs QLoRA to preserve object-level image understanding."
  ]
}